# SMTP Email Configuration for LEAP by LLL
# 
# These environment variables are required for the contact forms to send emails.
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual SMTP credentials.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env.local to version control!
#
# For Vercel deployment:
# 1. Go to your project settings in Vercel Dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Environment Variables
# 3. Add each variable below with your actual values
# 4. Make sure to set them for all environments (Production, Preview, Development)
# 5. Redeploy your application after adding the variables

# SMTP Server Configuration
# Example for Gmail: smtp.gmail.com
# Example for SendGrid: smtp.sendgrid.net
# Example for Mailgun: smtp.mailgun.org
# Example for Office 365: smtp.office365.com
MAIL_HOST=smtp.example.com

# SMTP Port
# Use 465 for SSL or 587 for TLS (recommended)
MAIL_PORT=587

# SMTP Authentication
# Your SMTP username (usually your email address)
MAIL_USER=your-email@example.com

# SMTP Password or API Key
# For Gmail: Use an App Password (not your regular password)
# For SendGrid/Mailgun: Use your API key
MAIL_PASSWORD=your-password-or-api-key

# Email Addresses
# Sender email address (from)
MAIL_FROM=noreply@lll.com.hk

# Recipient email address (to) - where form submissions are sent
MAIL_TO=leap@lll.com.hk

# ============================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================
#
# Gmail Setup:
# 1. Enable 2-factor authentication on your Google account
# 2. Generate an App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Use the 16-character app password as MAIL_PASSWORD
# 4. Set MAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com and MAIL_PORT=587
#
# SendGrid Setup:
# 1. Sign up for SendGrid: https://sendgrid.com/
# 2. Create an API key in Settings > API Keys
# 3. Use 'apikey' as MAIL_USER and your API key as MAIL_PASSWORD
# 4. Set MAIL_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net and MAIL_PORT=587
#
# Office 365 Setup:
# 1. Use your Office 365 email as MAIL_USER
# 2. Use your Office 365 password as MAIL_PASSWORD
# 3. Set MAIL_HOST=smtp.office365.com and MAIL_PORT=587
#
# Testing Locally:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your SMTP credentials
# 3. Run: npm run dev
# 4. Navigate to /get-quote or /contact-us and test the forms
#
# Troubleshooting:
# - If emails aren't sending, check your SMTP credentials
# - Ensure your firewall allows outbound connections on the SMTP port
# - Check server logs for detailed error messages
# - For Gmail, make sure "Less secure app access" is off and you're using an App Password
#
# ============================================================
